stylometry: The tradeoff/relationship between price and demand is that price determines demand. Unit price drives everything, but ultimately price determines demand. When price and demand are combined it can give the user the revenue, profit and costs. When setting the price of a product or service, it is very important for the management to make the decision not to set the price under the unit price, because then the company would not be making money. In means of developing a problem, it would be important to show the relationship of how price determines demand.  By showing this relationship, management could then make decisions regarding pricing, and how to maximize their profits for the demand in the market.
